      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The most robust affirmative case for increased border security rests on the principle that a nation has a sovereign right to control its own borders to protect its citizens and maintain national integrity. Strict enforcement is not merely a law enforcement tactic but a fundamental prerequisite for preserving the rule of law, as unchecked migration undermines the social contract and allows criminal networks to operate with impunity. Furthermore, prioritizing border security creates the necessary stability for the country to effectively process legal immigration and integrate new residents, rather than allowing the system to collapse under the weight of unmanaged flows. Ultimately, a strong border is the bedrock upon which all other immigration policies must be built to function effectively.",
