      "content": "that's a really solid foundation for them, thanks. one thing they're running into is that the opposition keeps hitting them with the \"humanitarian crisis\" argument—basically saying that strict enforcement is inherently inhumane/cruel. can you help them flip that? how can they argue that strict enforcement is actually the more ethical or morally sound path in the long run?",
